This paper is about improving Matrix Factorization (MF) methods for implicit feedback in online recommendation systems. The paper discusses the challenges of dealing with missing data and the dynamic nature of online data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with recommendation systems. The paper also proposes a new learning algorithm based on Alternating Least Squares (ALS), which is a popular technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the efficiency challenge of variably-weighted missing data, which is a common problem in Data Science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the online nature of the data and proposes an incremental update strategy, which falls under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two public datasets, which is a common practice in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
